This number of frames will be constructed equally distributed between x from the first positioning and xEnd.
Distance between the frames in x direction. The number of frames between x from the first positioning and xEnd will be calculated and constructed.
xEnd defines the x coordinate of the last frame element xStart is taken from the first frame positioning x value.

The frame definition can be used to define one or more fuselage frame elements. One frame element is defined by one or more positiongs and can be repeated within a x range ruled by a discrete number or a x spacing value.
